# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the portfolio project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed @vercel/analytics package
- Added `@vercel/analytics` version ^2.0.0 to the project dependencies
- Updated package-lock.json with the new dependency

### 2. Modified src/App.jsx
- Imported the Analytics component from '@vercel/analytics/react'
- Added the `<Analytics />` component to all route returns in the App component
- Wrapped each route return with a React Fragment (`<>...</>`) to include both the page component and the Analytics component
- This ensures analytics tracking works across all pages:
  - HomePage (/app)
  - AllProjectsPage (/projects)
  - ProjectDetailPage (/projects/:id)
  - GuestbookPage (/guestbook)
  - BookCallPage (/book-call)
  - Legacy page routes

## Implementation Details

Following the Vercel Web Analytics documentation for React applications, I used the `@vercel/analytics/react` package which provides seamless integration with React apps. The Analytics component is a lightweight wrapper around the tracking script that will automatically track page views and send data to Vercel's analytics dashboard.

## Build Verification

The project was successfully built with `npm run build` and no errors were introduced. The build output confirms:
- All 61 modules transformed successfully
- Production build completed in 1.18s
- No TypeScript or linting errors

## Next Steps

After deployment to Vercel:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics tab â Enable)
2. Deploy the app using `vercel deploy` or by pushing to the connected Git repository
3. Verify the analytics are working by checking for network requests to `/_vercel/insights/view` in the browser's Network tab
4. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics tab

